## Git Workflow

### Branching
- Work in git worktrees: `git worktree add -b <branch> /tmp/{{APP_NAME}}-<slug> main`
- Branch naming: `fix/issue-{N}-{description}` or `feature/issue-{N}-{description}`
- One branch per issue

### Commits
- Clear commit messages referencing the issue: `Description (fixes #N)`
- Run completion checklist before committing

### PR Submission Checklist (MANDATORY — do not skip any step)
1. Run completion checklist (format, compile, test, dialyzer)
2. Commit and push
3. Create PR via `gh pr create`
4. **Screenshots**: If the PR touches ANY `.heex` template or LiveView UI, capture screenshots and post as a PR comment. No exceptions.
5. **Self-review**: Spawn a fresh sub-agent to cold-review the PR diff. Fix all findings, re-review until clean.
6. Only then tell the user the PR is ready.

